... the psychological reason why they wait to the 15% drop to sell explained below:

$SPX$SPY$TSLA$QQQEvolutionary psychology explains how retail is walking into a totally obvious trap.  
 
Our brains are "economizing" machines. It does NOT want to expend energy thinking of particulars. It thinks in patterns long after the individual data points which produced Pattern One (uptrend), have all flipped to produce Pattern Two (downtrend).  
 
Change in patterning is our brain's weakness because doing so expends too much energy.
